  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Due to the HBV and HCV infection, about 55% hepatocellular carcinoma patients happened in
      China. Among them, only 10% patients can be diagnosed in early stage. Sorafenib increased
      PFS and OS in advanced hepatocellular carcinoma patients with liver function of Child-Pugh
      class A patients, but the result for Child-Pugh class B patients is unclear.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
